messages.content: You and Cyrus are back in the garden. Daryush and Azura are laying down on the floor unconscious and holding hands.
I shake my head to ground myself upon this world again. Urgh.
I look over at Cyrus. "Well, that... was enlightening?" I ask, a little worried about how he might be reacting to what he experienced.
"Yes. In a few ways."
I look at Azura. "What do you think happened with them...?"
"Beats me." I shrug. "Maybe they got emotionally exhausted yelling at one another."
I sigh. "I feel... exhausted."
I nod. "That was certainly a trying experience."
What time is it currently?
You canâ€™t see because the garden has a ceiling.
Shit, yeah.
"I feel like I gotta sleep... I've been going for a while now."
"Then, I think we gotta find a place to settle down for a while. It might be night already, so resting would be good." I then look at Azura. "Should we really be leaving them alone, though...?"
"We can just sleep here."
After a beat, "That's... a pretty smart idea, actually. It's pretty unlikely that the Wolf could find his way into here, right?"
"No guarantees."
"Then... I think I should stay awake for a while. Make sure he doesn't come by."
Ismalisa appears. "Do you two find yourselves closer to atonement?"
I jump, scared, again. "FUCKING SHIT- "
I flip around, instinctively feeling magic flow to my hands, though nothing comes of them. "A-Ah, uh, um... yes. I do." I nod.
After that, I look at her. "Y-yes. Yes. I do."
"Good. I am glad you are both finally making progress."

"I'm glad I can understand a little more about what's brought me here, goddess." I had forgotten so much of what had formed me. All of this... it was a lot to process, but it was certainly nothing I couldn't handle.
I keep quiet. *Finally*. As if I've not understood and regretted my actions since the second door.
"Midnight has passed long ago. You may proceed to the next doors if you wish."
((Forgot the timeline for a sec))
"I see. I just... need a while. I'm exhausted."
I'm tired too, but I don't want to leave these guys alone, even if I want to finish the doors out.
"I'll think about it." I tell Ismalisa a polite, white lie.
She vanishes.
((Hiiii))
((were we both waiting for one another lol
"I'm gonna sleep, I think..."
"Alright. I'll stay up for a few hours and wake you in a while."
"I'll make sure to keep watch when it's my turn." I drop to the ground and try to fall asleep.
After a few hours, Azura wakes up.
Azura is never manually awoken for some reason and just wakes up to find Cyrus asleep on the ground too now and Celine awake.
I'm pretty tired at this point, having watched over Cyrus, Azura, and Daryush for a few hours now, but I feel the need to at least converse a bit with Azura.
"Morning, Azura. How was your rest?"

Azura blinks up at Celine, mentally shifting through the things that've happened. *Haha. Fuck.*

"...Uninterrupted." She says delicately.
"Good to..." I'm interrupted by an unexpected yawn. "...hear."
Azura sighs, a bit put out. "Alright, you should probably sleep too. But first, can you tell me what's been going on....?"

"Well, Cyrus and I went through the door here, obviously. We found out a little more about what led us here. Um... what else... we fought that Wolf guy, not Johammad, but the one the chief was warning us about. He has a really scary sword, if I'm honest. He can slice us into bits and make us immobile. They don't hurt at all, but they paralyze us."
"Yes, that does sound like trouble."
"We did beat him, but... it took Ismalisa to actually do it. He got sent off the mountain, but he's alive, according to the goddess."
Azura scowls. "Why didn't she just do that in the first place?"
"Apparently she can't access the doors or something."
"That's stupid."

"Blame the system, I guess. I also don't know why she didn't just kill him if he's such a problem maker. Apparently it's against her moral code or something? Like, she doesn't decide our destiny here?"

"Hm. Yes." She smiles tightly. "Yes, killing people directly is against her moral code, isn't it? Permitting it, or allowing it to happen, is fine, of course. It only matters if she dirties her own perfect hands. Aha..."
"Whatever floats her boat." I sigh, shutting my eyes.

Azura sits in silence. She stares at her knees, folded on the ground. Thinking hurts, a sort of bitterness bulwarked by the memory of very fresh pain. 

Her brother sleeps on the ground next to her.

She leans over him, curious. Analytical. What features of her own can she see mirrored in his, should she choose to look?
Which brother?
*Oh hell, that's right. Two of them, now.*
Cyrus first.

He looks like this. If you had to say, he certainly looks more like your father than you do. But there are certain subtler similarities that you recognize within yourself as well. Things like face shape and eyebrows.

Azura tilts her head to the side, studying him intently. The shape of his skull, the jut of his forehead - even something about the way his ears jut out the side of his head - remind her, painfully, of herself. It's so strange. Is this real? Is she making it up? To feel some kind of connection? Anything?
She switches her gaze over to Daryush.

The resemblance to Daryush is much more obvious. You'd say your mother just has strong genes, if you didn't know about how heavily Ismalisa had gotten involved in your family tree. He lacks the iconic bright blue hair you have since that's exclusive to the women here, but he definitely looks like the spitting image of your mother and yourself in male form.

*Haaah. He's just like me. That's the trick, isn't it? It's because of narcissism, clearly. The roundness of his face is just like mine. The shape of his eyelashes are just like mine. The curve of his cheek - the rising and falling of his chest as he breathes - all mine, all mine, all mine. From the start I knew I wasn't whole. Couldn't be. They took a part of me and gave it another body. A male body. What do I provide, then? If he gives the orders, if he has the fluttering, transient heart of the Goddess inside him, what am I? The sex intended to produce female gametes, the ovum. The other half.*

*...Intended by who?*

*Ismalisa, surely. But she would deny me this? All I'm meant to be is...*

*I don't know. The sex intended to produce female gametes; that releases an egg during the monthly menstrual cycle. Intended, but not permitted. My soul is still and cold inside of me.*
Azura watches over them for as long as it takes for someone to wake up, knees pulled to her chest.
Cyrus and Celine finally wake up eventually.
I wake up. "Huh, whuh- Oh, good morning."
I also awaken. "Uwaaaa... morning, Cyrus."
"Good morning." Azura says soberly.
Is Daryush still unconscious?
Yes.
"Hi. We should get going." I get up, stretching.
"Are we just going to leave Daryush?"
"He's not awake yet." Azura says, gesturing to him.
I poke Daryush with my foot. "Wake up."
Daryush grumbles and slowly sits up. "Where am I? Oh, rightâ€¦ The garden."
"Cyrus and I got out of the door. It's the next day now, apparently."
"Ah. So we should all only haveâ€¦" He does some mental calculations. "2 doors, right?" He gets up and dusts himself off.
"Around that."
"Ideally, yes. That should be the case for everyone."
"Whereâ€™s Roshan right now?"
"Not here. We should go find him."
"Yeah." Daryush heads into the labyrinth.
I go with.
((Is everyone coming?))
Azura follows as well, silently.
I follow along as well.
((Roll investigation to solve the maze!))
The group manages to solve the maze and emerge back outside after a bit. "Alright, where was the last place you saw them?"
"The mountain."
I look to Cyrus, nodding in agreement. "We split up there, yeah."
"So we need to go back up there now?"
"I would normally assume they had made it down, but... who knows, with the Wolf around."
"Alright... Have any of you done the retribution door yet? I don't think you have, so we could just split up and meet up at the top of the mountain for whoever's using that door."
"I'd need Yazmine for it. I don't know where she is, either."
"I don't even know who I need for that. I forgot to check before we left the summit."
"Well, why don't you go check now then? If anyone's up there, just send them down with the info about who you need."
Azura remains silent.
"Good idea. I think I'll do that. You guys stay safe, okay?"
She nods.
After whatever Cyrus speaks, I depart for the summit with a brief wave.
"I'll just look for Yazmine, then."
"The rest of us can check the old man's cabin then. It's pretty close by." He heads towards there without waving to Celine.
Azura follows after him.
These two, then.
I look to Daryush. "You coming with?"
((Daryush is the one being followed Cina))
Clarification. I say this to Azura as he walks away.
"Yes."
Is Cyrus coming, then?
Yes.
They reach the cabin. Doesn't seem like anyone's around. "Alright, not here then. Village should be the next step. At least Ebrahim is definitely there."
I go there.
Daryush does as well.
Azura as well.
Roshan, Mohammad, Ebrahim, and L are all in the village. Yazmine and Douglas arrive at the same time as you do.
At some point, Yazmine must have fallen asleep, because she wakes up in the morning next to a campfire she doesnâ€™t remember building. Douglas is cooking some of the fish they caught.
â€œâ€¦eh? Oh. Uh, good morning.â€
"Hungry?"
â€œI could eat, I guess.â€ I donâ€™t think about why Iâ€™m hungry as I have some smoked whatever-is-around-here.
"Have you ever thought about what these animals are doing here?"

â€œâ€¦Not really, no. I guess I sort of just assumed they wereâ€¦ part of the package? Like, the same reason thereâ€™s trees, and dirt, and everything. I guess itâ€™s kinda weird when you think about it.â€
"Are they atoning for animal crimes perhaps?" He chuckles.
â€œHah. Sure, weâ€™ll go with that. â€¦Guess Iâ€™m cutting their atonement short, unfortunately.â€
Douglas finishes his fish as well. "So how was fishing? Was it nice to return to?"
â€œâ€¦Kind of, yeah. Relaxing. â€¦Thanks.â€
"My pleasure, Yazmine."
â€œSo, uhâ€¦ guess we can, head back to the villageâ€¦â€ I get up and stretch.
"I suppose so, yes." He puts out the fire.
I head there with him.
Roshan, Mohammad, Ebrahim, and L are all in the village. Azura, Cyrus, and Daryush arrive at the same time as you do.
You wake back up.
"â€¦mmmnnn." I yawn. Itâ€™s kind of dark under here, and I canâ€™t tell of Fours is still asleep. I should let them get their rest, in case they are.
I'm awake. But I do my best to pretend to still be sleeping. I don't want to get up just yet.
It's nice here. Both of us quiet and warm.

â€¦I think theyâ€™re still asleep. Well, thatâ€™s quite alright. Weâ€™re not in any hurry, are we?

I look at the gaps between the rim of the boat and the ground to see if the sunâ€™s risen yet.
I suddenly get a piece of fur caught in my throat and start choking.

Oh, gosh, what? Whatâ€™s this? Are they about to throw up or something? No, no, noâ€¦ my smell mustâ€™ve finally gotten to themâ€¦

"Fours!" I shout, turning their face up towards me. "Are you alright?"
"Khhh...!"
I hack a bit more and successfully get the hairball out. So much for peaceful slumber, I guess.
"Y-yeah. I'm fine. Thank you."
"Guess you just shed a bit more than I thought, haha."
I inspect my clothing and see some more fur stuck to it. I don't bother picking it off or anything, though.
"Yeah, my parents mustâ€™ve hired a guy to clean it all up or something. Maybe thatâ€™ll be the memory I get in the next door, haha."
"â€¦Good morning, by the way."
I smile. "Good morning to you too, Joey!" I decide on this cutesy thing for today, and then quickly hug him.
"Oh!-" Well, thatâ€™s a new one! Things really are moving very quickly. Maybe thatâ€™s a good sign. "Y- yes, right! Good morning, Foursies!" I return the hug, of course.
I canâ€™t believe this is actually happeningâ€¦
I don't immediately like the nickname, but I keep quiet. Maybe it'll grow on me. "So, um... what do you want to do today? What are our plans?"

"Iâ€¦ you know, now that you bring it up, Iâ€™m not actually sure Iâ€™ve ever had a plan. I sort of just enter a door a day, since itâ€™s always seemed prudent, and aside from that, stuff happens to me that keeps me busy."
"Ah... I see."
"I feel like a lot of the people we've met on this island are doing the same thing, to be honest. Just... assuming that this is all there is to do."
"Or, I guess, doing it out of prudency."
"â€¦Maybe youâ€™re right."
I scratch my chin. "What does prudent mean, again? I'm not sure I remember."
"Well, itâ€™s, umâ€¦ a word that fits the context, I believe."
"Oh, okay."
"â€¦Right. Well! All thatâ€™s to say my daily routine remains unchanged, if you donâ€™t have anything to add to it."
"We only have so many doors left, right? I think Iâ€™m going to goâ€¦ oh, oh dear. Iâ€™m going to have to convince Dad to open the village door with me next."

I hesitate a bit before speaking. "I'm not sure it counts as adding something to the routine, but what I was trying to imply is that... maybe we don't have to do this? Maybe we don't have to keep going in the doors? I mean... if we're happy here, then, well, I'm sure we can find some other way to occupy our time, right? Somewhere to explore that doesn't involve all this pain."
"You don't really seem excited to go see your 'dad', if that's... if it's okay for me to say that."
"â€¦Iâ€™m not. I think heâ€™sâ€¦ well, it seems like heâ€™s trying to be nice. But heâ€™s a very silly person in a way thatâ€™s caused me a lot of hurtâ€¦"
"Yeah, I assumed something like that was the case. So, why are you even bothering? Why do you think that door is going to make you so much happier that it would be worth it?"
"Have the other doors done that? Have you come out of each one more fulfiled than when you entered?"
"I just... that hasn't been the case for me. Not at all. Each one, I feel like all it does is weigh me down more and more. Pull me further away from myself, from... from you."

"...Well... not going through the doors for forever was kind of Dad's thing, now that I think about it. Maybe it would be nice, to... go through them all, and still come out the end okay. As a sort of spiteful gesture."

"Every door I've gone through only beats into my head what a failure I am... and how much I've been failed. A- and it doesn't seem likely that we've crossed paths before at this point, I have to say. So... you might be right, but..."

"I want you to think about it, though. Ismalisa said that when we completed all of our tasks here, we would leave. Where are we leaving to? I don't know much about the world out there, still, but I can at least pretty confidently say that it's large. That there are a lot of places to end up in. Do you think we even live on the same landmass? How could we ever be sure we would find each other again? Are you willing to risk that for... spite? For a gesture?"
"Maybe the best way to spite her would be... to not do exactly what she wants. What she told us to do. Perhaps it would frustrate her even more to just live, happily. Do you get what I mean?"

"...I think I do, yeah." I swallow my saliva, shuffling in place. "Still, living here happily isn't as simple as you make it out to be, right? The guy whose face I bit off is still out there somewhere, and very mad. Even after he's dealt with, there's no telling what else Ismalisa might do to us, as long as we're here..."

"Why are we so afraid of Ismalisa? The Wolf, I get. He's clearly a formidable threat, and willing to hurt us. But what has *she* done? The last real action she took was saving our lives. Before that, it was just trapping us here. Why are we assuming that she's going to do something to stop us from staying, and then... pretending like she's already done it? I don't know what motivates her. I don't know if she's even sane. But if she has some issue with us sticking around, shouldn't we let her tell us that herself?"

"...I suppose."

I hug Fours tighter. "I'm sorry. I know I said I'd be willing to work something out here if the next handful of doors didn't bring me any happiness, but I don't know what to do. I'm sorry. I'm not trying to be a bad person, or a beast, or anything like that, I just... I'm so scared."

"No, no! You don't have to apologize... it's perfectly okay." I pet him a few times. "You don't need to justify yourself to me. I get it. This is a confusing place. I don't really know what I want a lot of the time either. I just... whatever you choose, I want us to end up on the same path. That's all."
"We can go to your next door. I don't think I'm in a good headspace to keep doing mine anytime soon, but..."

"Can you just promise me that... if we end up outside again, in the world of the doors... that you'll look for me? I don't know how easy that'll be, but... I want us to try. I want us to know that we each care enough to try."
"...Yes. Of course! Y- you don't even need to ask, that would be my first order of business!"
"...okay. Thank you."
"I-I guess I should say that my full name out there would be Roshan Ghahremani. You probably wouldn't be able to find a Fours, even if I started going by it."
"Right. Good call. That should be an easy enough name to remember... Roshan Ghahremani... Roshan... Roshan..."
"Well, it's a very nice name to say, isn't it?"
"I don't really like it."
"What's yours, though?" I look at him curiously.
"It's... Mohammad. Don't you remember? The whole reason that I, that the..."
"Well, at any rate, I'm sorry you don't like it. I can just keep calling you Fours, if you prefer. Or whatever else you find pleasing."
"Oh, I meant, like... also your last name?"
"Oh! ...Chohaili. I think. I try not to think about that."
"We are... or we were a pretty important family, where we were. Not the hardest to track down, hopefully."
"Mohammad Chohaili. Got it!"
"It's a cute name. Very fitting for you."
"I... haha..." I'm blushiiing. "I don't know. I feel like every name sounds a little silly on me, at least of the ones I tried."
"Maybe I should test out more surnames."
"I guess, sure... it's not like anybody is calling you by your last name, though. Haha."
"Well, you don't know. Maybe someone considers Johammad my surname."
I quirk my eyebrow at him. "And why would they think that? That's awfully silly."
...I shrug.

I smile lightly and break the hug. "That's probably enough banter for now. If you want to make it to your next door today, we should get a move on. The sunlight seems to pass by before you even notice around here."
"Yeah, I was about to say. I feel like my limbs will all lock up if I stay under here for any longer."
"Let's go, then."
I shuffle out from beneath the boat, and lightly dust myself off afterwards. Standing up doesn't feel great. I really do miss the bed.
The boat does not lift up. Something seems to be above it weighing it down.
"...Mm?" I try a lot harder to lift it, then.
"Ugh. It's probably..."
I start shouting. "L! Let us out, you freak!"
"Jeez, you two love birds finally wake up?" L yawns exaggeratedly loudly.
I'm not claustrophobic, luckily, but the air is stale in here, and I don't appreciate this interruption of our plans.
"We- we've been talking for a while, you know!"
I try to lift it again.
It lifts this time. He's just standing on the side now with his usual hideous smirk.
I stand up, knitting my brow. "Were you really waiting for us?"

I pull myself to my feet, annoyed. "Don't engage with him, Jo, he's just trying to get under our skin. Don't let him and he'll go away eventually." I head over to the water's edge to splash off some of the sand that's caking my body.
"What else was I supposed to do? No one's doing anything."

I shout to Fours in the water. "No, I mean, this is weird, though! We were here because we didn't want to be found, you know? You can't just...!"

I turn back to L. "We weren't doing anything under there either!"
I roll my eyes. "He was already here last night, Jo. I didn't really care if we got found."
"And we WERE doing things under there. We were doing A LOT."
"I'm sure L would love to hear all about it. Right, L? In scandalous detail?"
I scratch the side of my neck.
"I don't care what kind of bone you feed the wolf, kay? What matters is gathering everyone together again for the next doors."
"That's not even- god, you're disgusting, you know that?"
L bursts out laughing.
"Yeah, I'm... I'm not an animal. I don't eat bones..."
"That... he..." I look at Jo with a mixture of confusion and pity. "Whatever. Do you want to wash yourself off, Jo, or should we get going?"
"Oh, uh..." I look over my shoulder. "I'm not sure. When I jumped in the ocean fully clothed, that was sort of a desperation thing. I'm probably fine, for the time being."
"Alright. I think... um... would your 'dad' be in the village, by the door that you need him to open?"
"If I had to guess, yeah."
"Great."
"Yeah, heâ€™ll be there."
I ignore L, walk over to Jo, take his hand, and start treading towards our destination.
I'm also walking and handholding!
L follows. You arrive at the village. Inmate 01 is indeed still here.
I didn't realize that this was who he was talking about. What did Jon call him? Ibrahim? Ebrahim?
Well, I'll let Jo start the conversation and figure it out from there. He's the one who wanted this, after all.
He looks at you silently.

I look back at him, and realize I'm still holding hands with Fours.

"Um... hi."
"Do you... um... c- could you, you know... that's to say, L's going to be upset if we don't..."
"...You want me to go in the door, right?"
"...Yeah." My gaze turns down.
"Why do you... Want to see what's in there so badly, son?"

......

"I don't know. Why do you want to stop me from seeing what's in there?"
"You were a mistake, Mohammad." He pauses. "...But you were my mistake. I'm tired of making mistakes."

.........

What an...

"...awful thing to say..."

No, no, come on. You can't start crying now. Seriously? When you put up such a brave face in front of the kidnapper, and... and...
I squeeze his hand comfortingly. You can do this, Joey.
"I know it's never been your fault, Mohammad. You're a good person. That's what you've always been. I fucked you up."
I squeeze my free hand over my face, trying to stifle the tears. "I- I don't... I don't..."

"I always called you a bad omen, Johammad. That's what I thought of you as. But the truth is, I don't think that's what you are. You weren't a warning. You were the karma. There was no message of warning, just you coming in to show the world how far our city had fallen. To show them that the great protector was a fraud who'd cost them everything. I don't think it's a coincidence I'm Inmate #1. All of this... It's about me. I brought sin into our city. I brought you in."

"...What do you... even mean..."

I can't stop it. Why do I have to be a symbol? Or... a thing? Why can't I just be me?
"I mean that... I don't want you to hate yourself anymore, Johammad. I'm the one who fucked everything up. I'm the one who always fucks everything up. And I'm... So tired."
I whisper to him. "You're not a fraud, Jo. The great protector was never a fraud to me."

"...thank you," I whisper back. I'm not sure if it's legible. I really do appreciate it, even if it feels... a little hollow, for some stupid reason. It's probably nothing.

"I- I don't understand what you're getting at... they're punishing you by giving me a life of nothing but misery? It plainly doesn't make sense... and they're punishing you for, what, failing to give me a good life? Like I said all that time ago, that would be recursive..."

"Everything I've done in my life has been a mistake, Mohammad. You were just the capstone on my long and arduous descent towards this... Sinspace. Even our leader, Cyrus... His mother died because of my failure. There's a million reasons I fear that door... But no matter what I know all that awaits beyond it is failure. It's all I can do. It's all I am."

"So... what? You're scared? That's it? You think another reminder of what a bad person you are to add to the pile makes any difference?"

I wheeze, and blink away the next round of pooled tears. "Sorry... I'm really, really sorry... I didn't mean it like that, I swear, I just..."

...I don't know what to do. I can't see any way of convincing him to open the door. Maybe I'll just stop.

"Relax, he'll come around soon." L smirks. "After all, the pressure he needs is arriving."

Yazmine and Douglas arrive from the direction of the cliffs. Azura, Cyrus, and Daryush arrive from the direction of the mountain.
â€œOh, everyoneâ€¦â€ I mutter, staring at the ground.
"What...?"
I decide to stop saying anything.
Azura is here.

"What... Do you mean?" Ebrahim.

"Heyyyy, Cyrus. Mind doing us all a favor?" L is grinning.
*I fucking hate this guy.*
Thereâ€™s a conversation. I guess we showed up in the middle of it. Ok.
"What?" I sound curt and annoyed at him.
I let go of Johammad's hand. "Um... why is..."
*Why are they holding hands? Are they gay?*
I look around uncomfortably. "Big reunion, huh? Just missing... Celine..."
~~Itâ€™s like weâ€™re in some king ofâ€¦ everyone except 59â€¦~~
"Hm." Azura smiles without humor.

"Use your wise leadership powers... And make him open the door with Mohammad." L.

"Wh-What?" 01.

Yazmine doesnâ€™t say anything. 63 doesnâ€™t say anything. I donâ€™t say anything.

â€¦What door? Powers? What the fuck is he talking about?
*See, okay, so, why do people call him Mohammad? I thought his name started with a J?* Azura has this important thought.
I sigh. "So what's going on here, Ebrahim?" I preemptively also say "Shut the fuck up, L, I want to hear it from his mouth." In case he starts speaking first.
"Nothing. Nothing ever happens." Ebrahim.
I give him a stern look.
He doesn't elaborate.
I sit down on the ground.
I sigh. "I'll guess, then. Jo and you need to go to a door together. However, you refuse to do so, and now, you're at an impasse until you do?"

â€œWhat the fuck do you mean wise leadership powers, heâ€™s a beneficiary of nepotism in a place we currently arenâ€™t, that doesnâ€™t make him, like, magicâ€¦â€ I stop holding this back. Iâ€™m still basically looking at the dirt.
"I think he's being sarcastic." Azura helpfully provides.
"We don't... really need to go through the door. But I don't think L will be happy if we don't."
63 shrinks back.
I wince. She's not wrong. But I really did try so hard.

"Exactly. Cyrus has no power here." Ebrahim looks away.

"Would you say the same to his mother's ghost?" L winks hideously. 

Ebrahim goes silent.
"Don't fucking say that."
"That was my fault, and none of his."
*Aha. Wow. What the fuck.*
I kneel next to Jo and start speaking with him softly. "I thought this is what you wanted? We agreed... that this is how you would prove that you could still be okay. Have you changed your mind?"

â€œMan, if heâ€™s number 01, did likeâ€¦ was there always a requirement to enter the door with Jo? Even before he showed up here? If not, would the contents of the door have been different? And if it is, what if one of us is blocked by likeâ€¦ some future guyâ€¦â€
"...I don't know. I really, really don't know."
I think L is the first person I've met who tempts me to do the opposite of whatever they ask of me.
"Yeah. I understand. It's okay to be indecisive. All it means is that you're willing to think things through. I'm sorry if I... rushed us into this."
"...it's alright. It was going to happen today either way."

"The door requirements change depending on who's around." Daryush.

"You sure, Cyrus? Wasn't that long ago that old Ebrahim admitted all of that was his fault. How noble of you to take on his burdens then, huh?" L.

"Shut up!" Ebrahim shouts. "It was... It was all my fault, Cyrus. You don't... You don't have to lie."

â€œUm. By the way, is L real? Have any of you been able to confirm that? Azura staggers over to the corner and throws up. *Why? I don't understand why that happened. That doesn't make sense.*
"Oh, um... he- hello...!"
"Uh... is she okay? Do either of you- well, I guess you wouldn't know. What's going on, Azura?"
I approach her cautiously.
"I can... Make some guesses." Daryush doesn't look at Azura directly.

She slumps against the back wall of the cave.

*That's Roshan. He's walking towards... Azura. Okay. Is a thing going to happen? Is something going to happen? I don't know. This isn't what's supposed to be going on. I don't react to things this way.*

She blinks cautiously at them, silent.
Well, I... I stand up, at least.

*That's Daryush. Daryush is talking. The only important person... is talking.*

"Y-yes." She says. "Um, I... don't really know, why this is, um, I feel, um,"

*What's happening here? She teases him and everyone else. She's ridiculous, and probing, and aggressive, sometimes without cause. She only gets all fidgety and flinchy like this when snapped at. Nothing's occurred. What...?*

"I'm sorry?" She says it like a question.
"...Sorry, but is there something to be sorry about...?"
"We could... go back to the water's edge, if you want something to wash your mouth out with..."
I'm trying to be helpful.
"Ah, yes..." She says distantly. "I should do that..."
Daryush holds out his hand. "I'll help you stand if you need it." He's still not quite looking at her though.

Azura makes... a motion, at his gesture. Her body shudders all over. An immediate, terrified flinch.

*Okay, what the fuck.*

She shakes herself as if to shed it all, like water, like a coat of skin she no longer needs, and takes his hand. "Thanks."
It... for a moment there, it really... looked like she was scared of something? I don't know why, but I feel like I should... do... something.

"Um, you know, Dar, how about I take her over to get that water? Maybe... maybe you and Jo could stay here and talk for a bit. It feels like the two of you... haven't really had much of a chance to get to know each other, right?"
I smile at him lightly.
"...I guess that's true. We haven't really... done any of that."
"Uh... Do you want that, Azura?"

*Why is he asking me? He's not supposed to. He's just supposed to make the decision and I go along with it. That's the whole point! That's what I was urging him to do this entire time! Surely that's why I was punished earlier, right? Ismalisa was hurting me for the crime of overstepping, of proposing something I didn't have the right to propose. All things in time. I know Azura... I know Azura threw a fit during that other dream, the first time she experienced that specific kind of memory, but I'm not her anymore! That girl wasn't real, anyways. She was a hollowed-out shell without the required memories that would make her whole. I'm working towards being better than her, so I don't... why would I, like... it's what I wanted, but couldn't say, right? That's all he's ever done. He understood my emotions before I did, and acted on them.*

None of these thoughts actualize. Instead, Azura opens and closes her mouth for a few seconds, like a fish on the hook. *Maybe.. if I go with Roshan, we can um, talk? I can ask him to clarify the situation with regards to his relationship, and Johammad, and whatever... Yazmine insinuated, earlier.. yes. That's right. I'm not scared. I can be away from Daryush for a minute. I mean, now I know, right? From that memory, I know I don't need to be working tirelessly to stake my claim on him, or anything. I already have it. Right? Yeah, okay. That makes sense. To talk. I want to be around Daryush, I do, obviously, but it won't kill me to not, be, um..*

She nods. "Uh, yeah. I'll go with Roshan."
"Okay! Good... cool." I reach out my hand for her to take.
She takes their hand gingerly.
"Umm... Alright then." Daryush lets go, looking confused.
I walk out towards the beach with her, glancing back at Jo and Dar to make sure they aren't objecting.
I give Fours a little wave goodbye.
"We'll... we'll stay back here! Until you're ready to sail back! Or, uh. I guess not sailing. Rowing. Haha."
I give him a thumbs up with my free hand before turning back.
Azura silently follows Roshan out.
((oh ok bloop said brb))
I lead her to the water, and wait for her to do her thing.
Azura leans down, cups some water in her hands, and swallows it. It's cold. Refreshing.
"Oh, um. I wasn't expecting you to drink it. I think that's saltwater?" I grimace.
"I mean, if it tastes fine..."
((I thought it was a freshwater lake lmfao))
"It's fine." She coughs. "I'm fine."
"...okay. If you say so."
I lean down and pat her on the back a few times.
It's awkward.
The touch surprises her. Her body startles away from it again.
I jerk my hand back. "S-sorry! I'm sorry. I didn't mean t-to surprise you." I back away guiltily.
"I just. Um. I guess I'm not familiar with your boundaries yet. Since we don't know each other that well."
She blinks. "My.. boundaries?"
"Yeahh..." I put my hand on the back of my neck. "Ah... you know. Like, I'm not sure what I can get away with yet. Or, no, sorry, bad way to put it. I'm not sure... what you're comfortable with."

"Um. What?" She's confused. "Am I just supposed to list everything that weirds me out or something...? What if I said my 'boundary' was that I didn't want to go through the dumb doors?" Something about this conversational path is irksome to her. "I don't get what you're concerned over..."
"No! That's not what I was saying... I just... ugh. Isn't it okay for me to apologize for something without there being a problem that we need to figure out how to fix?"
"You don't have to list anything. I just- I already said it. I would need to get to know you more. That's all."
Maybe this was a mistake. But I can't really back out now, can I? I work to gather my thoughts on what I brought her here to say. It's okay to feel this way. It's okay to be afraid.
I look around, as if somebody might be listening in on us. "Can I level with you, Azura?"
"Um.. okay?"

I sigh. "I know what happened between you and Daryush. I'm not here to get mad at you for that or anything. Like, I get it. Trust me, I get the appeal there. That's not really what I want to talk about. I just-" I wave my hand around a bit. "I think I need to do a better job of processing what's been happening to me in these doors. I want to be okay with it, instead of constantly avoiding it and shutting it out. Everybody else around here seems to be doing a better job of that than me! So, I... there's one thing I keep coming back to. I spent a lot of time with your brother. And that time was meaningful to me. It was meaningful to me back then, and it's meaningful to me now, and it's, like... it clearly plays into the feelings of who I am now, who I am today. And one of the things that defined my time with him was, I guess, that I was always... jealous. Jealous of you, of the time Dar spent with you and what the two of you had. You know? And you clearly still have something going on. I saw how you reacted to him back there, that shudder. I know what that's like, haha, that... specific emotion. Um, anyways. Not the point. The point is, I know that... Daryush had a troubled upbringing, a troubled household. It was one of the things that I always bonded with him over, actually. And my past self, Roshan, they just weren't able... weren't willing to extend that same sympathy to the *other* people in that situation. One of their blind spots, I guess. I know that you're the one who banished him from the church, so I can understand the visceral reaction there, but like, honestly, I didn't even want him in the church! So, it was probably a bit hypocritical of me anyways, and, this was clearly going on before then, so I don't even know why I'm bringing it up. I was- uh, yeah, right. I know that you had a difficult time, and I would really like it if we could... appreciate that fact together, and maybe that could help me move on from this hangup of mine. Okay?"
I realize that I've been rambling for a while, and get a bit embarrassed again.

Azura's eyes go wide. 

*I know what happened between you and Daryush. I know what happened between you and Daryush. I know what happened between you and Daryush. I know what happened between you and Daryush. I know what happened between you and Daryush.*

"Um." She clears her throat, scared stiff. "I don't know what, you, I..."

She lurches forwards, uncontrolled, and grabs Roshan by their collar. "Youu..! How many people know?? Does *everyone* know???? No, no, this can't be happening.. I, my fucking, I, I, I'm... I'm the Holy Maiden, okay?!? A fake one, a bullshit one, but I can't, like, be this, I can't, I'm..." She's choking back sobs, now. Pathetic. "It's not fair! He was the only person I fuckin' had, okay, that was the only option, that was the only thing that was ever going to happen, that he would... I didn't, I didn't make him, okay, it was a m-mutual, mutual, I..." She's almost incoherent. 

Her hands... slump. "Did you sleep with him?" A demand, bitter, miserable. "Were you two laughing behind my back the whole time?? Jealous of me? Why would you ever be, I mean, how could you ever... I never even, I couldn't give him what he wanted, not one fuckin' thing, he always had to take it, I'm a dipshit asshole, I'm not the, I'm not, the, fuckin'-" This incomprehensible babbling continues on for some time.
What? What? What's going on? What did I do? I thought- I didn't realize that she was this... unsteady on her feet... I just...

My mouth opens and closes a few times, the same as hers did before. I don't understand almost anything she's saying. Fake? Unfair? Mutual? It slides off of me, barely collecting into anything I can actually examine. But I understand that I've done something wrong. I've hurt her. And she's standing in front of me, sobbing. So, I do what I would want done to me, and I wrap her tightly in a hug.
"No. I didn't sleep with him. He's not... gay."

A human launches out of the water and lands next to them. "Jeez, ladies. There's enough of me to go around for everyone!" The Wolf has arrived. The Wolf is a pale white young man with a manic grin and missing a nose. He's wearing a suit of red armor and a flipped back hood. In his hand is bizarrely large weapon which if Azura knew modern technology she would label a weird chainsaw, but alas it just kind of looks like an incredibly odd weapon with a bunch of knives on the front. He takes off running towards the inside of the cave.
"WHAT!" Azura screams in shock. The hug was really nice, actually, even if it was with a man other than Daryush, which she'll.. unpack. Eventually. "Who the fuck is *that*?!?"
I manically untangle myself from Azura and start sprinting after him. "It's The fucking Wolf, Azura! He's going to kill Dar and Jo! We can talk later! Come on!"
"That's not a wolf! That's a human!" She protests, but follows them in.
The Corruption door is gone. Otherwise the 3 people you would expect to be here are indeed here.
"Uh... Do you have any idea what that was about?"
"...With Azura?"

"And Roshan. I should know both so well by now but Roshan seemed so... Panicked? About this? Was it just because Azura looked scared? She always looks scared. I know I haven't been... Good to her. But that's who Azura is. Azura needs me when she's hurt. It should've been more reason to go with me." Daryush ponders this. "She's had her chances to be free and every time she runs back to me. I don't... Know how to deal with her anymore, I guess." 

"You do, Inmate 34." Ismalisa appears with a stern expression.

"Oh, um. N- no, I don't think I'd know anything about tha..."

I'm cut off by the appearance of Ismalisa, but... I don't have anything to say to her. At least nothing worth cutting off her conversation with Daryush.

Daryush doesn't look at her. "I'm not inclined to trust answers that were tortured out of me."

"What about you, Inmate 60? Do you feel any closer to atonement?" Ismalisa.

"...Mmnngg. I don't know..." I sit on the ground again, because what else would I do here. Of course. "I... I might get it, on some level, maybe. It just... seems so cruel of you to do things like this. Do you really think I deserve this...?"
"That depends on what you mean by 'this'." Ismalisa.
"I don't know, this whole... format. Drip-feeding me glimpses of the awful things I've done, slowly picking at all the spots in my brain that I thought were nice, and safe, and..."
"...It's just horribly inefficient. Like you're torturing me on purpose."

"That is not the intent." Ismalisa.

"So you're just an idiot? Is that your excuse?" Daryush.

"The process of self-improvement requires looking back on one's past." Ismalisa.

"Why do we need multiple doors? Just- just put it all in my brain at once, and then maybe... I'd be able to untangle it all... but as things stand, I'm thinking... you're flipping my mindset around over and over again, because you hate me, a- and you want to see me hurting..."

"On this island... You are perhaps the one I hate the least, Inmate 60." Ismalisa.

"What? Really? How could you hate Azura or Roshan more than him...?" Daryush.

I ignore what Daryush said.

"Then why... why can't you just put an end to things?! Tell me what I'm doing wrong?!"
She disappears.

...

"Ugh." I run a hand down my face. Just... wasted energy. I don't understand. I don't usually shout like this, right? So why can't she spare me just a little more. What even was the point of showing up like this?

...I need to keep being nice. That's all I've ever needed. I'm so, so sorry.
Daryush groans. "Insufferable woman."

I breathe in. I breathe out.

"Yeah."
"I hated her before I actually met her, just... Off the church stuff. Can't say I've become any more of a fan."
"Is... is she some sort of God? I mean, I already knew that, but... do people actually worship her like one?"
"Yeah. Me and Azura were raised by her holy maiden until... Azura became the next one."
"...The next Ismalisa?"

"The next Holy Maiden. It's... Basically the Holy Maiden is like Ismalisa's wife? And then they have a child and that child becomes the next Holy Maiden. Obviously there's important priest duties but it goes beyond the normal things you'd expect of a priest."
"Oh." I scratch the side of my neck, looking away. "That feels awfully predatory, don't you think?"
"Well... Yes, but in what sense specifically do you mean?"
"The whole... existing to become a specific person's wife thing. Or God, I guess."
"You ever heard of the concept of soulmates? I don't think that part's too bad."
"...Maybe I've read it in a book or something. I don't know, though. That feels different."
"With this kind of stuffâ€¦ I think you just learn to get over it."
I look down. "...That's sad."
"Is it? It's... Love."
"Maybe. If you really think so. Sad love."

"..."

Unthinkingly, I step outside, going back to where we docked our boats.
As Johammad heads to leave, The Wolf bursts into the chamber. "You..." He snarls at you.
(from what direction?)
(the direction he was headed?)
((Yeah there's only one exit))

Oh, no no no no no. Not now. Why...?

Stumbling back, I shout: "F- fffff- Fours! He's back! He's back...!"

"Shit... Him again." Daryush.

The Wolf swings his blade at the door and shoves it into the bag carved out of reality Johammad saw him use on the retribution door. 

Roshan and Azura arrive.
The Wolf waves mockingly.
Azura is here. "Aaaah!!! What the fuck!"

I pull out my axe, obviously, and position myself closer to the entrance while I have the chance.

"Don't try anything funny!" I shout at him. I'm... surprised at my own conviction?
It's time. It's finally time. I ready myself for the big battle. My heart is jackhammering in my chest, and my palms are already starting to sweat, but I'm going to give this my all.
We need to get out of here, *now*.
"Weahhhgh....."

Ismalisa appears. "Would you like a repeat, Inmate 0?"

The Wolf growls. "I'm done all the doors and I haven't entered any recently. You can't hurt me. But... The good news is you won't have to. A lot of you fuckers tried hurting me last time... So I'll be going all out. With *all* of you. I've taken all the doors, so none of you have any choice now. Come to the beach at sundown and get ready for the fight of your fuckin' lives! Gyahahahaha!" His weapon carves a hole in the ceiling that seems to bend reality itself. "This is the big one, so don't bore me. I wanna see what the goddess does when she's all alone! And Mr. Wolfman's reaction when I carve his friends up oughta be priceless too!" He jumps through it, causing it to close behind him.
"Weh?"
I raise one of my daggers and point it at Ismalisa. "We don't need you to defend us from the likes of him, whore."
...I put my axe away silently.

"A rather rude statement. I assume you are no closer to redemption, then?" Ismalisa.

"Well... Our mother was the whore, not Ismalisa, but whatever..." Daryush mumbles this pointless correction.
I lower my dagger and look at him, confused. "What? That's- what are you talking about? Your mother *is* Ismalisa. That's the whole- huh?"
"Well, her too... In a sense. But I meant the holy maiden before Azura. Did you- Not get that?" Daryush.
"I think it's a two moms situation. I don't entirely get it, but..." I look at nobody in particular.
"Umm.... yeah. Ismalisa is kind of, my dad... except she isn't... ahaha..." Azura mumbles, miserable.
"What about you, Azura? Do you find yourself any closer to redemption?"
"...It seems really odd, to me. But I guess I can't judge, if it's love..."
I cock my head, trying to square this new information with what I know about my life.
Azura just wraps her hands around herself. "Was it because I was presumptous...?" She asks, miserable. "To want...? Was it that *he* had to offer, first?"

"â€¦Iâ€™m sorry."

I donâ€™t know why Iâ€™m apologizing. Haha.

"Your very relationship is filth. Family is not built for that structure." Ismalisa.

"Says the woman who bangs her fucking daughter every generation!" Daryush.

Ismalisa doesn't respond.

I'm really caught up on this, for some reason. Ismalisa has faded into the background. "Dar, you told me that we were doing our performances to let people know that your mother was a whore. Why would that not be talking about Ismalisa? I didn't sing about your birth mom."
Azura's eyes scrunch up, upset. "Then what the fuck else was I supposed to *do??* I didn't know anyone else! There was never anyone else for me to love!"

"The Holy Maiden is the main priest of the church. She's the one people actually feel connected to." Daryush.

"You are not to love. You are to remain pure, remember? As goddess I took it upon myself to replace all men in your life to maintain your purity." Ismalisa.

"Then what about me, huh!? Why the fuck did you create me!?" Daryush. Ismalisa doesn't respond, so he continues, stepping closer. "Come on! Fucking tell me! Why did you create me if you've got this obsession with Azura! If you loved her so much, you shouldn't have made the fucking competition! Now you've got no one left to love you. Your people are fucking corpses and the only ones left who believed in you *hate* your fucking guts. You're not anything anymore. So do us a favor and fucking die in obscurity! You're an unlovable abomination who never had the right to call itself divinity. If we lived in a world of moral gods, none of this would've happened! You ruined our lives and then get on our high horse about how our misery hurts you because we made some bad choices. Why don't you put on the fucking inmate outfit and remind yourself in short bursts why you're a miserable failure who's hurt the lives of everyone who knew she existed? Maybe then you'd get to say shit about how much a sinner the people here are. Because for now, the only sinners on this island are me, you, and the fucking wolf." 

She responds to this rant by simply vanishing.

â€¦â€¦â€¦

"Heyâ€¦ Fours?"
I'm still confused, and trying to word my next question, but I stop for the moment and turn to Jo. "Yeah?"
"Daryush..." Azura says, taking a step towards him. Her expression is empathetic.
"â€¦Our relationshipâ€¦ umâ€¦ it isnâ€™t going to end up anything like this, right? Like Azuraâ€™s and Ismalisaâ€™s."
A look of vague disgust comes to my face. "No, Joey, I don't think there's any chance of that happening. No chance at all."
"â€¦Okay." I huff. "Thatâ€™s good. Thatâ€™s reassuring."
"What?" Azura says, confused. "How is that even comparable...?"
"If I had an issue with you, I would just tell you about it. I wouldn't trap you on an island to torture you." As fun as that might sound, in concept. Without the torture part, of course.
"Don't worry about it, Azura." Daryush holds her hand. "Come on, let's go back to the beach. We should probably warn everyone about the wolf."
"â€¦Right. Thatâ€™s good. I wouldnâ€™t do that to you either. Weâ€™ve had enough islands for one lifetime, haha." I squeeze out a chuckle.

She squeezes his hand, reassuring. "You know you're not a sinner, right...? You don't deserve to be grouped in with her. It's not your fault you were made incomplete. She's the one that did that, alongside how she cursed *me.*" She sighs. "And then she has the audacity to chastise us for wanting to become whole..."
"To become... Whole." He doesn't answer beyond this, simply starting to walk out with Azura.
"Well. I suppose we ought to head back now as well... right?"
She follows.
I also follow, even if I feel as though we haven't resolved everything I wanted to resolve.
((End session))
You arrive back at the little port. The boat situation hasnâ€™t changed.
so thatâ€™s to say we have boats right
Yes.
Azura climbs into a boat.
Daryush gets into Azuraâ€™s boat.
((Actually thereâ€™s only 2 boats I just remembered Douglas left. So it did change a bit technically))
I... get into the other boat, looking uncomfortable.
I follow Fours into said boat and sit down.
"â€¦Letâ€™s get to it, then."
Azura patiently waits for Daryush to begin rowing.
Daryush rows back to the beach.
I also row! Back to the beach!
I take the right paddle, letting Jo handle the left one.

messages.content: You arrive back at the beach. Since the sun is still up, there's no wolf around.
I get out of the boat, and scan the area, in case any of the others are around.
Azura does this also.
Only you 4.
I shake my head and try to remember what we were all doing.
"So, wait. Daryush, earlier you told me that you had gone through the death door, right? And it was your childhood? Is that true?"
"I think that's the only door I have left. Honestly, I was feeling a bit paranoid about... dying. But if that's not even what happens in it..."
"It's a metaphorical death. The loss of something core to your identity."
"Hm." I consider it. "That's almost scarier."
"I've already lost a lot of my identity. This whole island has been the slow process of losing it, really. If I had to manage a vision of that new part of me being broken... eugh." I shudder.
"Maybe I was right to not want to go through all of them."
"...It's alright. You won't see me past that door, Foursies. Nothing in our pasts can change the fact that we're here."
"Yeah... I appreciate it, Joey." I don't want to say that it's not him I'm worried about being behind it.
I put my hand on his shoulder.
"What do you want to do next? I'm feeling kind of lost. We came here to warn people about The Wolf, but I can't put my finger on where anybody would be right now..."
*Gay people...*
"I was going to say the village was our best bet. It seems like it's become our hub of operations."
"I agree with Jo."
"Okay."
"Alrighty. Let's get going, then."
I pull my hand down and start walking, I guess.
"Yes, let's." I pat Fours' shoulder in turn before following them.
Azura trails behind.
Celine, Douglas, and Ebrahim are there. The birth door is gone.
Wait, so is L.
Tragically forgettable guy.
Celine makes it up to the top of the mountain after a while. There's nothing here but the retribution door.
I go and touch the knob of the Retribution door.

"You have reached the door of Retribution. Rejoice, after climbing the tallest mountain your comeuppance has arrived. You are not tainted by any door yet today. Your requirement to open this door, Inmate #059, is none." The door opens.
I enter the door.
((End session since you said you had to leave))
((alright, ty
((we are so back

This door picks up from your memories of the Growth door. You spend years getting to know the orphans of Site 17 and training them as they get sent off to kill others. It's a natural rhythm at this point. It's how things should be, perhaps. After a long day of work training them, you find yourself back in your room.
I sit down at my desk and log a little bit about the week's events, journaling about my thoughts on recent events.
There's a knock at the door.
Getting up, I check whoâ€™s at the door, opening it.
It's one of the younger kids. "Mommy...? There's something outside."
I lean down. â€œAre you sure itâ€™s not just the wind? Tell me about it.â€
"I think I saw something on the beach..." That's definitely very odd.
I furrow my brow a little bit. â€œHow about I go check it out, okay? You can head back to bed. Thanks for letting me know.â€ I ruffle their hair a little.
"Okay!"
"Good night, kiddo." I lock my room's door behind me, then head outside, wary of whatever might be lurking out here.
There's a small boat washed up on the beach. Nothing about it is particularly notable, but it definitely shouldn't be here.
I slowly approach the boat, keeping an eye on it and on my surroundings to ensure I'm not ambushed. It's very possible this is a straggler washed ashore, but I can never be too careful.
There's nothing inside.
Upon seeing that there's nothing inside, I turn to go back to the facility. I need to keep an eye on things from inside and make sure no one's breaking in.
As you return, the child who alerted you goes flying out the window, clearly injured.
"Shit!" I yell, rushing in towards that child's bedroom.
The entire inside of the building is like a massacre. All of the children are trying to murder each other.
I desperately try to call for everyone's attention. "STOP! STOP!" I yell out.
"Stay back, mother." "Get out of the way!" "This isn't about you." You get similarly dismissive responses from everyone as this massacre continues.
"What's happening?! Tell me!" I demand from some of the children.
You don't get a meaningful response. Bodies simply start piling up.
I begin to despair as I see more and more kids die. I slow down in my attempts to stop, slowly having it sink in that there's nothing I can do.
One of the kids sneds out a burst of flames, igniting the building rapidly.
Seeing as the flames are growing bigger, I run as quickly as I can to my room to try and salvage my journal. Curse my choice to lock it earlier, as it's slowing me down a little bit.
You make it there.
Quickly, I scramble to grab my journal, before getting out and trying to escape with my life.
The injured child you saw earlier crawls towards you as you exit.
I immediately drop down to his side. "Kiddo, please, you gotta stay with me, yeah?"

A stone spike impales him. You jump backwards in shock... And then the memory you have seen before occurs once more.

You are sobbing next to a burning building. You hear more fighting inside but you cannot bring yourself to do anything. You see one of your children laying impaled in the entrance and it kills any strength you may have left to enter the building and attempt to end the fighting. Some part of you tells you this is your fault but you simply cannot understand why. You want to be anywhere else. You cannot handle this. This thought causes a familiar power to surge through you. The sensation of your sorcery skills only sicken you even more, however. You need it gone you need it gone you need it gone. You scratch away at yourself fruitlessly to tear away whatever part of you is doing this. It's pointless, however. As you watch the corpse of one of your older children be tossed through an upstairs window the power of wild magic surges through you and explodes outwards desperately. You are a sorcerer now.
With tears trailing down my face and despair wracking my heart, I begin to hyperventilate, letting loose magic escape from my body.
Incomprehensible effects occur all around you as your mind is flooded with rage and misery. You need to go in. You need to stop this. To understand what is going on.
Trying in vain to steel my nerves, I take in a breath, walking towards the building, seeing if there's anything left for me to do.
